                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="193988" author="bfaccini" created="Sat, 29 Apr 2017 08:52:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for a master patch/review :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a709de32-2c8d-11e7-814a-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/a709de32-2c8d-11e7-814a-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="121639" author="di.wang" created="Sun, 19 Jul 2015 15:43:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close it for now, since this failure does not happen for almost 2 months. Reopen it when it happen again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116469" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 27 May 2015 00:19:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The OI scrub logic is relatively independent. Unless some patches introduce or potential cause more background workload (consuming CPU, I/O bandwidth), otherwise, the OI scrub speed should not be affected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116448" author="di.wang" created="Tue, 26 May 2015 20:35:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not sure about other failures. But this failure happens with only two tiny patches, i.e. no major DNE patches there yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14679/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14679/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14678/7&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14678/7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this probably not because of DNE patches. And I only saw this one time during all these tests.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116420" author="adilger" created="Tue, 26 May 2015 17:24:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My concern here is that the DNE changes are slowing down the system somehow, and that is what is causing these different related test failures, since they aren&apos;t being seen by any other code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116353" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 26 May 2015 03:29:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test failure means the scrub speed in not as good as the expectation. I did not check your patch carefully, but I think it should be more related with the test environment. It is not strange that the performance is bad under VM environment. Since it is not correctness issue, you can adjust the speed expectation range or skip this failure directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116342" author="di.wang" created="Mon, 25 May 2015 17:48:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fan Yong: could you please advise here? Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
